b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Process Street is best suited for operations teams, onboarding, compliance, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Relay.app, meanwhile, shines for teams needing approval flows, operations, customer success, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2014, Process Street describes itself as \"AI-powered workflow and checklist platform for recurring processes.\" Relay.app, established in 2021, positions itself as \"Automation platform with human-in-the-loop approval workflows.\" With 7 years between them, Process Street brings the maturity and proven track record of a veteran platform, while Relay.app offers the fresh perspective and modern architecture of a newer entrant."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Relay.app** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (9 vs 8), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Process Street is a poor choice — far from it. Process Street excels in its own right, particularly for operations teams and onboarding.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value unique human-in-the-loop approach, go with Relay.app. If excellent for documenting and running processes matters more to you, Process Street is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
